{
  "stem": "12053.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And she had been searching, researching for many, many years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And she found her mother's maiden name, Bechhofer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I said, if you give me written permission that I may broadcast the name or-- or write about it, I might-- I'll try and help.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "My sister got broadcast on Kol Israel radio.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I went to Israel during that year.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We broadcast the name with the result that Susi, who didn't know if she was Jewish-- she didn't know who she was-- she has a large orthodox family in New York.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "The BBC made two films of her life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "It touched-- it had great repercussions, her life story.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And she is a completely different person.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "I've felt rather guilty what I've done to her, because it turned her life upside down.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "She played the church organ.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "She was a committed Christian.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Now she's learning what it's like to be a Jew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "It's not an easy life for her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "But she-- and she's not the only one.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "There's a most wonderful story, also somebody who phoned me up, who was a little bit older who knew that she was Jewish, Gwen Richards in Devon.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And she had been adopted by the Christian family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And she said, still in my heart, I still feel like a Polish Jewess.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And she wrote me her story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And for her, I found I had a-- by the time we became known as having a reunion, with a bookstore and everything, I had a letter from a Professor Schwartz in Jerusalem.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And he put a note in that his wife had written in, and she wrote the following-- I'm the only survivor of a very large family from Poland.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "I was taken by the Germans with my large family into a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
